A low-pass filter is an electronic filter that allows low-frequency signals to pass through while attenuating higher frequencies. It is commonly used in audio applications to remove high-frequency noise or to create a "bass boost" effect. The filter's cutoff frequency determines the point at which signals begin to be attenuated.
